            {
              "kind": "narrator",
              "path": "/people/narrators/19",
              "text": "أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام )"
            },
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ],
          "text": "عَلِيُّ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ عَنْ أَبِيهِ عَنِ النَّوْفَلِيِّ عَنِ السَّكُونِيِّ عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) قَالَ"
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:22:1",
        "text": [
          " إِذَا دُعِيَ أَحَدُكُمْ إِلَى طَعَامٍ فَلَا يَسْتَتْبِعَنَّ وَلَدَهُ فَإِنَّهُ إِنْ فَعَلَ أَكَلَ حَرَاماً وَ دَخَلَ غَاصِباً ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When one of you is invited to a meal, so he should not let his child follow him, for if he does, he would be eating unlawfully, and would enter as a usurper’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from af-Nawfafiy from af-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘When one of you is invited for food do not allow your children to follow you, because in doing so he eats unlawfully and enters (the house of host) as a usurper.’” "
          ]
        }
