              "text": " قَالَ"
            }
          ],
          "text": "مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى عَنْ أَحْمَدَ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ عَنِ ابْنِ أَبِي عُمَيْرٍ عَنِ الْحُسَيْنِ بْنِ أَحْمَدَ الْمِنْقَرِيِّ عَنْ خَالِهِ قَالَ"
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:22:2",
        "text": [
          " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ مَنْ أَكَلَ طَعَاماً لَمْ يُدْعَ إِلَيْهِ فَإِنَّمَا أَكَلَ قِطْعَةً مِنَ النَّارِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Al Husayn Bin Ahmad Al Minqary, from his maternal uncle who said, ",
            "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The one who eats a meal he had not been invited to, so rather is eating a piece from the Fire’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn abu ‘Umayr from al-Husayn ibn Ahmad al-Minqariy from his maternal uncle who has said the following: “I once heard abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ‘If one eats a food to which he is not invited he eats a piece of fire.”’ "
          ]
        }
